{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I thought this problem simply in terms of areas. A square can have areas of 1, 4,9,16,25....49 etc.. Since we have 49 squares, we can take the square root. Giving us 7 squares per row. Since its an odd number, we simply go to the middle row and column, which corresponds to 25."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"9+1 =10, and then 10 divided by 2 equals five. 49+1=50, then 50 divided by 2 = 25"}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice also that the middle number is equal to the quotient of sum of one vertical, horizontal, or diagonal numbers of the square and the square root of total numbers of squares. (For 3x3 square: sum of each line = 15. square root of total number of squares = sqrt(9) = 3. 15/3 = 5) So for 7x7, 175/7 = 25."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It should be average of 1st and last number in every case.....it is as simple as that!!"}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If there's a 7 x 7 arrangement, the middlemost column would be the column containing 4. Now, looking row-wise, the middle most row will be the fourth one. Suppose the middlemost number is in the nth   row. Then, we'll have to add 7*(n-1) to 4. Thus, we get the central number as 4 + 7(3) = 4 + 21 = 25."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

