{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We realize that "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"49=7^2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" thus if we find a number that has all the digits which are the same and is divisible by "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"7"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" we can multiply that by "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"7"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and it will still have all the same digits. Thus by inspection we see that "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"111111"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is divisible by "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"7"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" thus our answer is "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\frac{7*111111}{49}=\boxed{15873}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}}]},{"type":"text","text":"



